# Production CORS Configuration Example
# Use this as a template for production deployments

# Production web applications
https://restaurant.example.com
https://admin.restaurant.example.com ALLOW ALL content-type,authorization,x-api-key
https://pos.restaurant.example.com ALLOW POST,PUT,GET content-type,authorization

# Kitchen systems (local network)
http://192.168.1.100:3000 ALLOW POST,GET content-type,authorization
http://192.168.1.101:3000 ALLOW POST,GET content-type,authorization

# Cashier terminals (local network)
http://192.168.1.110:8080 ALLOW POST,PUT,GET content-type,authorization,x-terminal-id
http://192.168.1.111:8080 ALLOW POST,PUT,GET content-type,authorization,x-terminal-id

# Display systems (read-only)
http://192.168.1.120:4000 ALLOW GET
http://192.168.1.121:4000 ALLOW GET
http://192.168.1.122:4000 ALLOW GET

# Mobile applications
app://restaurant-mobile ALLOW ALL
capacitor://localhost ALLOW ALL

# Block known bad actors (examples)
http://badactor.example.com DENY
http://spam-crawler.net DENY

# Deny all other origins by default (uncomment in strict production)
# * DENY